          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r0212eca8f29e4c77b1f10359ede56916:44125293c84e",
            "label": "Proposed language (must be less than 1000 characters):",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9,000,000,000 for the National Aeronautics and Space Administration Science Mission Directorate.\n* This funding supports the implementation of Decadal Survey priorities across Planetary Science, Astrophysics, Earth Science, Heliophysics, and Biological and Physical Sciences.\n* Investment provides critical resources to maintain the U.S. aerospace workforce and advance scientific discovery at institutions including Florida Atlantic University.",
            "rationale": "This language follows the standard programmatic request format for NASA Science, explicitly stating the $9 billion ask amount and referencing the Decadal Survey priorities that guide SMD funding. It also connects the funding to local workforce benefits at Florida Atlantic University as identified in the spending context.",
